all this to say i'm starting 2022 exactly how i've started the last two years: taking my year long plans, break them into tasks for 12 months, and then for jan and feb, break those into doable action items on a week-to-week basis.

i also only allow me to stick to a given task for an hour at a time. my brain WANTS to jump around, so i let it. if i don't finish the task, i bump it a few spots on the queue to return to. this, of course, is adjusted in cases of major deadlines, but good for day-to-day stuff
